+    fun `Issue 1324 - Given an already wrapped nullable function type then do not report unnecessary newline before opening parenthesis`() {
+        // After wrapping a nullable function type, the inner opening parenthesis should not be flagged
+        // as having an unnecessary newline before it. The whitespace before the inner '(' belongs to
+        // the nullable type wrapping, not to the parameter list.
+        val code =
